#  Changelog v2.3.1 (SNMP container permission fix):
#   - Dockerfile: KaSaNaa's snmp_manager.py logs to ./logs/snmp_errors.log
#     (relative to /app); the non-root user could not create it, crashing
#     every run with FileNotFoundError. Now create /app/logs owned by the
#     scanner user at build time.
#   - Image tag bumped latest -> 1.1 so the fixed image rebuilds
#     automatically (ensure_image skips rebuild when the tag already exists).
#
#  Changelog v2.3.0 (SNMP probe -> ephemeral detection container):
#   - probe_snmp() REWRITTEN: the local snmpget/snmpwalk + Python heredoc
#     probe is replaced by an ephemeral Docker container built from
#     KaSaNaa/SNMP-Network-Discovery. Proper SNMPv1/v2c/v3 (USM authPriv)
#     support -- fixes detection of the SNMPv3-only FortiGate.
#   - snmp_disco_ensure_image(): builds netbox-disco/snmp-detect:latest once
#     (multi-stage, pysnmp-only, non-root); Dockerfile embedded in-script.
#     Override image/ref via SNMP_DISCO_IMAGE / SNMP_DISCO_REPO_REF.
#   - snmp_disco_run(): runs --rm --network host container per host; v2c
#     communities tried first, then SNMPv3 USM creds from the store.
#   - KaSaNaa JSON mapped into the existing snmp.json contract (sys_descr,
#     sys_oid, chassis_serial, interfaces, ip_table, lldp/cdp neighbors,
#     entity_inventory). Container's Device Type / Manufacturer / Model
#     carried as kasanaa_role/_manufacturer/_model and used in
#     merge_host_data() as fallbacks AFTER the OID/keyword classifier.
#   - Graceful fallback: if docker is absent or the build fails, probe_snmp
#     marks SNMP unavailable and the scan proceeds on nmap/ssh/winrm tiers.
#   - NOTE: ipForwarding / Printer-MIB / hrDeviceType OIDs are not collected
#     by the container, so those signals are False under SNMP now; OID-table
#     and keyword classification (which identify the FortiGate) are intact.
#
#  Changelog v2.2.15 (soften ipForwarding hard rules -- regression fix):
#   - merge_host_data(): REMOVED the Router->Switch demotion that fired when
#     an OID-classified Router did not expose ipForwarding. Many routers and
#     firewalls (e.g. FortiGate) do not return ipForwarding or the SNMP get
#     times out, which was demoting correct OID matches to Switch. The OID
#     prefix match is now authoritative; ipForwarding is a hint only.
#   - merge_host_data(): the last-resort ipForwarding=True Router fallback
#     now also requires NO host-OS indicators (no SV keywords, no "linux",
#     no "windows" in OS) so Linux boxes, Docker hosts, and hypervisors that
#     enable IP forwarding are not mislabeled as routers.
#   - Printer MIB / hrDeviceType Tier-0 check retained (safe, definitive).
#
#  Changelog v2.2.14 (improvements from KaSaNaa/SNMP-Network-Discovery):
#   - probe_snmp(): ipForwarding/Printer MIB/hrDeviceType OIDs added;
#     Printer MIB/hrDeviceType = Tier-0 definitive printer classification;
#     Router OID + ip_forwarding=False demoted to Switch; ip_forwarding=True
#     as final Router fallback before Endpoint
#     ******** BROKE DETECTION ********
